Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ improve list - Version 6</span><hr size=1> Spouting that bs in more threads Filan? Removing the spell dmg nerf would be insane.  Lures hit for a lot regardless of resists and some classes have less than uber hp less than 1700 in pvp gear as a 57 rogue. Wizards around my lvl can more than likely absorb more nukes than I can with their hp + spellshield.  Wizards do NOT need the ability to kill me in 2 casts of lure of ice (or hell one if they get a crit) to be balanced. <br>
<br>
Thank god they annouced mannaburn is due for nerfage but that still leaves the 2 1/10 of a second gates that will make wizards effectively unkillable once they have them.<br>
<br>
See my suggestion for spell dmg percentage tables.  It goes as follows.  Each class gets a series of table based on lvl range. The level ranges for int casters would be...<br>
<br>
1-19, 20-29, 30-39, 40-49, 50-54, 55-60<br>
<br>
priest classes would be slightly different<br>
<br>
Each table would look like this...<br>
<br>
Wiz 1-19 Table<br>
Dmg vs wizards x% of full dmg in pvp<br>
Dmg vs enchanters x% of full dmg in pvp<br>
Dmg vs mages x% of full dmg in pvp<br>
Dmg vs necromancers x% of full dmg in pvp<br>
Dmg vs warriors x% of full dmg in pvp<br>
Dmg vs rogues x% of full dmg in pvp<br>
Dmg vs monks x% of full dmg in pvp<br>
Dmg vs rangers x% of full dmg in pvp<br>
Dmg vs paladins x% of full dmg in pvp<br>
Dmg vs beastlords x% of full dmg in pvp<br>
Dmg vs shadow knights x% of full dmg in pvp<br>
Dmg vs bards x% of full dmg in pvp<br>
Dmg vs druids x% of full dmg in pvp<br>
Dmg vs shaman x% of full dmg in pvp<br>
Dmg vs clerics x% of full dmg in pvp<br>
<br>
This would allow them to precisely tune dmg rather than just nerfing it to 66%.  <br>
<br>
In addition I think individual spells should have 2 new attributes.<br>
<br>
A) pvp dmg modifier so that single spells could be tuned to be stronger or weaker<br>
<br>
B) pvp resist modifier to give players more or less chance to resist the spell, I believe there is allready a general attribute that is similar but that it effects both pvp and pve which doesn't allow accurate tuning for pvp.<br>
<br>
C) set resist lvl modifier to be used in place of attribute B for 50+ spells that would set the base lvl of resist for a spell.  In other words the 54 druid nuke scorae would always hit as if the target has x lvl of resist.  X being a number that is fair for all parties.<br>
<br>
This set of suggestions is a much better solution than messing around with the modifier for resist debuffs in pvp helping some spells to much some to little.<br>
<br>
The second attribute even adresses an enchanter concern with NOTHING landing.  If spells had attribute B certain spells could be given inherently less resistance when used in pvp without making them more powerful in pve or raising the pvp resisted debuff modifier (currently all resistance debuffs do 1.5 normal when used in pvp) to such a ridiculous extent that enc end up blinding, rooting, and owning people.<br>
<br>
In addition the first attribute would provide a clean way to remove mannaburn from the pvp environment as verant has stated is neccesary.  Simply set attribute A to 0% of full dmg in pvp.<br>
  <br>
<br>
On the subject of charm in pvp.  There is absolutely no way it could be made non exploitable.  You could still /pet attack a friend and have that friend drag the player down into a dungeon.  <br>
<br>
Besides that I understand it was badly bugged.  I haven't witnessed it personally but I heard that besides pet attacking a guard it was possible to give no drop items to a charmed player because they were counted as an npc besides using /pet get lost to instantly cause them to suicide.  Pvp for verant is a small portion of their customer base more than likely even if they thought charm in pvp was a good idea fixing it might be more trouble than its worth.<br>
<br>
You might actually be completely missing the point besides that it could be that verant feels that charm like fear was too powerful and inapropriate for pvp which is my opinion personally.<br>
<br>
Another thing that could be done would be to make HT do a maximum of some fixed percentage of a players hp.<br>
<br>
Another thing is that I do not believe that all classes should be able to shadowstep via the mask from luclin.  On pve shadowstep is something of a toy in most situations as it will easily get you into more trouble than it saves you.  On pvp it amounts to a major class ability calously distributed to every class.  I know that there are ss items for rogues in kunark however the casting time + the fact that rogues lack any channeling skill + the inability to do any dmg from range effectively makes this useless both to do dmg and to escape as my own too feet are a more reliable means of transportation by far if I have to run.<br>
